Use an Alias for a Salesforce CRM Connection

As of July ‘24, an alias is required when setting up a Salesforce CRM connection. Existing connections aren't assigned an alias. The names of the data stream and data lake object are derived from the alias.

When you create an alias for the Salesforce CRM connection, the default data stream name and data lake object name are appended with the alias that you create. For example, if the connection is to the org MyCompany and the alias is SourceOrg, the data steam name and data lake object label is MyCompany_SourceOrg.

For connections that were created before the alias feature was available, no alias is assigned and the default data stream name and data lake object API name are appended with the org ID of the data source. For example, if the connection is to the org MyCompany and the org ID is 00DOK00129XWZ, the data stream name and data lake object name are MyCompany_00DOK00129XWZ.

By default, your home org connection is given the alias Home when the org is provisioned with Data Cloud

CRM Connections in Sandbox

When a Sandbox is created and provisioned with Data Cloud, the Salesforce CRM connections are copied over from the production org in the Inactive state. 

You can choose to activate the connection to either the same (1) data source org as in the production org or a different (2) one. When activating the connection, the alias is read only and can’t be modified. 

For connections that are copied over without alias, the org ID of the data source from the production org is used as the alias when you activate the connection.
